A HARARE man who masqueraded as Vice-President Constantino Chiwenga's close aide has appeared in court facing chargesof impersonation and domestic violence. Lloyd Mutotote, who is being represented by Tapson Dzvetero appeared before magistrate Dennis Mangosi for bail application.   It is the State’s case that sometime between February and May this year, Mutotote, who is a general hand in the Central Intelligence Organisation, masqueraded as an intelligence operative saying he was attached to Chiwenga’s office as a close aide and was attending to his business and private functions. It is also alleged that on a date unknown to the prosecutor, Mutotote assaulted his wife and pointed a fire arm at her. A report was made to the police, leading to his arrest.